# codename_generator

A Python version of the NPM package  [codename-generator](https://www.npmjs.com/package/codename-generator) and inspired by [codename](https://github.com/and3rson/codename)

Some ugly words have been removed (gross, underwear), we may remove more in the future.

## Installation

`pip install codename-generator`

## Usage

```shell
codename_generator
```

Or in code:

```python
from codename_generator import generator
generator()
```

## Development

```shell
pip install -r requirements.txt
python setup.py bdist_wheel

# elsewhere, install the version you just built:
pip install codename-generator/dist/codename_generator-1.1-py3-none-any.whl
```

Bump the version number on any changes, following semver

Then have @wheresalice run:

```shell
python3 -m twine upload  dist/codename_generator-*
```

